            <bio>
               <p>
                  <bold>Nicholas Serruys</bold>is a professor of Québec Literature and Culture at McMaster University in Ontario. His area of research focuses on speculative literary genres, especially utopia and science fiction. He is the author of a number of articles; the most recent is on<italic>Les Voyageurs malgré eux</italic>[Travelers Despite Themselves] by Élisabeth Vonarburg. He is presently working on a book-length manuscript on the vehicle as metaphor for progress or deviation in contemporary Québec science fiction.</p>
